meta {
  name: Ingest Document
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/documents/ingest
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "text": "Archon is a retrieval-augmented generation system built with FastAPI, PostgreSQL, and pgvector. It ingests documents, splits them into token-based chunks, generates embeddings for each chunk, and stores them for later semantic retrieval. When a user asks a question, the system embeds the query, retrieves the most relevant chunks by cosine similarity, builds a grounded prompt, and asks an LLM to answer using only the retrieved context. Citations are validated against the retrieved chunks, and a semantic cache avoids recomputing answers for near-duplicate questions.",
    "document_id": "doc-architecture-overview",
    "chunk_size": 500,
    "chunk_overlap": 50
  }
}

docs {
  ## Ingest Document

  End-to-end ingestion for a full document: splits `text` into token-based
  chunks (`chunk_text`), generates embeddings for every chunk in a single
  batch request, and batch-inserts them into the `embeddings` table.

  ### Request body

  | Field           | Type   | Required | Default | Description                                              |
  |------------------|--------|----------|---------|------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `text`           | string | yes      | ‚Äî       | Full document text to chunk, embed, and store.              |
  | `document_id`    | string | yes      | ‚Äî       | Logical identifier shared by all chunks of this document.   |
  | `chunk_size`     | int    | no       | `500`   | Target chunk size, in tokens.                                |
  | `chunk_overlap`  | int    | no       | `50`    | Token overlap between consecutive chunks.                    |

  ### Response `200`

  ```json
  {
    "document_id": "doc-architecture-overview",
    "chunk_count": 1,
    "inserted_ids": [1],
    "message": "Document ingested successfully"
  }
  ```

  | Field           | Type      | Description                                   |
  |------------------|-----------|-------------------------------------------------|
  | `document_id`    | string    | Echoes the request's `document_id`.              |
  | `chunk_count`    | int       | Number of chunks produced from `text`.           |
  | `inserted_ids`   | int[]     | Primary keys of the inserted `embeddings` rows.  |
  | `message`        | string    | Human-readable confirmation.                     |

  Note: chunking is token-based, not character-based ‚Äî very short input may
  still produce more than one chunk, or a single chunk smaller than
  `chunk_size` if the text doesn't reach the target length.
}
